pullrequest.title: Simple port of existing PERFORMANCE test as BENCHMARK

content.raw:
Result comparison \(note that numbers are different because benchmark is running 100000 internal iterations\)

Benchmark Results:

```
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Benchmark                                                   Time           CPU Iterations
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BM_Naive/100000                                             0 ns          0 ns 1000000000
BM_Expect<ExpectString>/100000                          67125 ns      67062 ns      10393
BM_Expect<Expect3Types_Leading>/100000                 101811 ns     101750 ns       6847
BM_Expect<Expect3Types_Trailing>/100000                102848 ns     102737 ns       6881
BM_Expect<Expect10Types_Leading>/100000                103229 ns     103121 ns       6808
BM_Expect<Expect10Types_Trailing>/100000               102586 ns     102525 ns       6730
BM_Expect<Expect20Types_Leading>/100000                104099 ns     103910 ns       6753
BM_Expect<Expect20Types_Trailing>/100000               103078 ns     102968 ns       6812
BM_Expect<ignition::physics::CompositeData>/100000    2551553 ns    2548902 ns        276
```

Existing performance results:

```
 --- 1 expectation result ---
Avg time: 0.567675 ns

 --- 3 expectations (leading) result ---

 --- 3 expectations (ending) result ---
Avg time: 1.783938 ns

 --- 10 expectations (leading) result ---

 --- 10 expectations (trailing) result ---
Avg time: 1.776774 ns

 --- 20 expectations (leading) result ---
Avg time: 1.775410 ns

 --- 20 expectations (trailing) result ---

 --- No expectations result ---
```
